-- Essar Communications Takes Full Control of Kenya Unit, Business Daily Says
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-11-30T05:55:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-30/essar-communications-takes-full-control-of-kenya-unit-business-daily-says.html
Essar Communications Holdings Ltd.
has increased its stake in  Essar Telecom Kenya Ltd.  to 100
percent from 80 percent, Business Daily reported, citing Jos
Konzolo, one of the Kenyan shareholders.  Essar Communications bought the 20 percent stake that was
locally owned by Capital Africa, CrossLink and Startnet
companies for an undisclosed sum of money, the Nairobi-based
 newspaper  said. Essar Telecoms Kenya Managing Director Atul
Chaturvedi said he didn’t know of the shareholders and that the
20 percent local ownership is held by the company’s lawyers,
Anjarwalla and Khanna Advocates, Business Daily said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 